title: The Hardy Boys Mystery Series by Franklin W Dixon (Books 1-48, 5
description:
Franklin W. Dixon is the pen name used by a variety of different authors (Leslie McFarlane, a Canadian author, being the first) who wrote The Hardy Boys novels for the Stratemeyer Syndicate (now owned by Simon & Schuster). This pseudonym was also used for the Ted Scott Flying Stories series.
The Hardy Boys, Frank and Joe Hardy, are fictional characters who appear in various mystery series for children, teens and young adults. A new Hardy Boys series, the Hardy Boys Casefiles, was created in 1987, and features murders, violence, and international espionage.
